{"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"set(returnOnCancel:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"returnOnCancel","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO12TaskProtocolPAAE3set14returnOnCancelS2b_tF","extendedModule":"GIO","role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskProtocol\/set(returnOnCancel:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/taskprotocol\/set(returnoncancel:)"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets or clears "},{"code":"task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s return-on-cancel flag. This is only"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"meaningful for tasks run via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_run_in_thread()"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_task_run_in_thread_sync()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"returnOnCancel","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"returnOnCancel"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", then cancelling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" will immediately cause it to return, as though the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"task’s "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc"},{"type":"text","text":" had called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_return_error_if_cancelled()"},{"text":" and then returned.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This allows you to create a cancellable wrapper around an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"uninterruptible function. The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" just needs to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"careful that it does not modify any externally-visible state after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it has been cancelled. To do that, the thread should call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_task_set_return_on_cancel()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" again to (atomically) set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return-on-cancel "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" before making externally-visible changes;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if the task gets cancelled before the return-on-cancel flag could","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be changed, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_set_return_on_cancel()"},{"text":" will indicate this by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can disable and re-enable this flag multiple times if you wish."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the task’s "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable","type":"reference"},{"text":" is cancelled while return-on-cancel is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", then calling "},{"code":"g_task_set_return_on_cancel()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to set it "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"again will cause the task to be cancelled at that point."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the task’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is already cancelled before you call"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_run_in_thread()``\/g_task_run_in_thread_sync()"},{"text":", then the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" will still be run (for consistency), but the task"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will also be completed right away."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskProtocol"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TaskProtocol/set(returnOnCancel:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets or clears "},{"code":"task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s return-on-cancel flag. This is only"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"meaningful for tasks run via "},{"code":"g_task_run_in_thread()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"c